<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,701,1047]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,741,767]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male FW length range 37.5– 
<quantity box="[686,770,741,767]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 mm</quantity>
(based on specimens in Appendix 
<number box="[1195,1209,741,767]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
). Wings with dark brown background. FW with a conspicuous, broad, white postmedial band and three subapical white spots. HW with a faded submarginal band. Males have a HW discal cell hairpencil and a scent-pocket. Ventral HW with a faded white postmedial band distal to the eyespots. Male genitalia more delicate than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1341,1436,861,886]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syme">
<emphasis box="[1341,1436,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. syme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[200,317,901,926]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcius">
<emphasis box="[200,317,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. sulcius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females similar to, but paler than males dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
